{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:28:11.321Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypedDict describes the shape of dictionaries with required and optional keys \u2014 ideal for chat messages, tool payloads, and API responses. Optional and Union types model missing values and alternatives explicitly, reducing bugs when parsing model output and constructing function-call schemas."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "TypedDict and Optional: typed agent message structures with required and optional key patterns"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypedDict", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "typing.TypedDict", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") declares expected string keys and value types for dict-like objects. "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Optional", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is shorthand for "}, {"type": "text", "text": "T | None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 a value may be present or absent."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from typing import TypedDict\n\nclass ChatMessage(TypedDict):\n    role: str\n    content: str\n\nclass ToolCallPayload(TypedDict, total=False):\n    name: str\n    arguments: dict[str, object]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLM APIs represent messages as JSON objects with string keys. TypedDict lets you document required keys ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "role", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "content", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") and optional keys ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "tool_call_id", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") without converting every message to a dataclass. Static checkers flag typos like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"contnet\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and missing required fields at development time."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "JSON-shaped typing", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 matches wire format for chat and tool calls"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optional keys", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 "}, {"type": "text", "text": "total=False", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Required/NotRequired", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (3.11+)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lightweight", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 still plain dicts at runtime; no conversion overhead"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No runtime validation", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 TypedDict does not enforce keys when constructing dicts"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extra keys allowed", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 TypedDict is not closed by default (see NotRequired patterns)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not a replacement for Pydantic", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 use Pydantic at API boundaries for validation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Required and optional keys"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from typing import TypedDict\n\nclass Message(TypedDict):\n    role: str\n    content: str\n\nclass AssistantMessage(TypedDict, total=False):\n    role: str\n    content: str\n    tool_calls: list[dict]  # optional when total=False for all"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python 3.11+ Required / NotRequired"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from typing import TypedDict, Required, NotRequired\n\nclass ToolCall(TypedDict):\n    name: Required[str]\n    arguments: NotRequired[dict[str, object]]\n    id: NotRequired[str]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optional and Union"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def get_tool(name: str) -> dict[str, object] | None:\n    return REGISTRY.get(name)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from typing import Literal\n\ndef parse_finish_reason(raw: str) -> Literal[\"stop\", \"tool_calls\"] | None:\n    if raw in (\"stop\", \"tool_calls\"):\n        return raw\n    return None"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Nested TypedDicts"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "class FunctionCall(TypedDict):\n    name: str\n    arguments: str  # JSON string from model\n\nclass AssistantTurn(TypedDict, total=False):\n    role: str\n    content: str\n    tool_calls: list[FunctionCall]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypedDict", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for message lists, OpenAI-compatible payloads, config dicts"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optional / | None", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for missing tool results, failed lookups, unset config"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataclass or Pydantic", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " when you need methods, validation, or serialization helpers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to implement"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "class GenerationConfig(TypedDict, total=False):\n    model: str\n    temperature: float\n    max_tokens: int\n    stream: bool\n\ndef merge_config(base: GenerationConfig, overrides: GenerationConfig) -> GenerationConfig:\n    merged: GenerationConfig = dict(base)\n    merged.update(overrides)\n    return merged"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def build_messages(system: str, user: str) -> list[Message]:\n    return [\n        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system},\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user},\n    ]\n\nmsg: Message = {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}\n# msg[\"rol\"]  # mypy error: unknown key"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-world example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typing the agent state dict passed between orchestration steps:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "class AgentState(TypedDict):\n    run_id: str\n    messages: list[Message]\n    tokens_used: int\n    last_error: str | None\n\ndef step(state: AgentState, user_input: str) -> AgentState:\n    state[\"messages\"].append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_input})\n    ...\n    return state"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assuming TypedDict validates", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 {\"role\": 123} passes at runtime; mypy catches it"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "total=False misuse", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 makes all keys optional; use Required for mixed required/optional"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optional[T] vs T | None", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 equivalent in 3.10+; prefer "}, {"type": "text", "text": "| None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for readability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Confusing None default with Optional field", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 optional key absent vs key present with None value"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Define TypedDict per message/response shape in a shared types module"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Required", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "text": "NotRequired", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for precise optional keys (3.11+)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Validate external JSON with Pydantic; use TypedDict for internal typed dicts"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prefer "}, {"type": "text", "text": "str | None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " over "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Optional[str]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " in new code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison with alternatives"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataclasses provide objects with defaults and methods; TypedDict stays dict-compatible for JSON APIs. Pydantic models validate at runtime and export JSON Schema \u2014 better at HTTP boundaries. Plain "}, {"type": "text", "text": "dict[str, Any]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is flexible but documents nothing."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Security and reliability"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explicit optional types force handling of missing tool results and failed API fields. TypedDict plus static checking reduces key typos that could cause agents to read wrong fields from parsed model output."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypedDict is a "}, {"type": "text", "text": "form template", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for dictionaries \u2014 it lists required and optional fields. "}, {"type": "text", "text": "| None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " means the field may be empty or the lookup may fail; handle both in agent error paths."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypedDict types JSON-like message and tool structures"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Required/NotRequired or total=False for optional keys"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optional means value may be None \u2014 distinct from missing dict key"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Combine TypedDict internally with Pydantic validation at external boundaries"}]}]}]}]}}